summary: I could totally see Moomintroll adopting a bunch of kids.  Between his father being an orphan, his parents adopting a lot of...
body:
I could totally see Moomintroll adopting a bunch of kids.  Between his father being an orphan, his parents adopting a lot of different people into their family (such as Sniff and Little My), and his overall nature to help those in need (such as Ninny), he would be all for adoption and making sure all of his children get the love and attention they deserve.

I’m genuinely surprised that Snufmin shippers don’t do this type of family dynamic more often; give me a happy Moomintroll, Snufkin, and their lovely children of all species! (because you know Moomintroll would adopt a Booble if he could, and Snufkin already adopted the Woodies so…)

summary: Moominvalley in November hurts so much more when you come to the realization it was written after Tove Jansson’s mother had...
body: Moominvalley in November hurts so much more when you come to the realization it was written after Tove Jansson’s mother had passed away, as many of the themes in the last books reflect how she had been feeling. (Primarily missing home, childhood, and themes of loneliness.) Moominvalley in November had been the last book she ever wrote as she felt she couldn’t return to that ‘happy Moominvalley again.’
